---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import TopicNext from '../../components/TopicNext.astro';
import MadeByKaj from '../../components/MadeByKaj.astro';
import TopicSkykitViewer from '../../components/TopicSkykitViewer.astro';

const title = 'What is nearby in space?';
const summary = 'A tour of the Solar System, the nearest stars, and the idea of a local stellar neighbourhood.';
const nextTopics = [
	{ slug: 'how-far-is-a-light-year', title: 'How far is a light-year?' },
	{ slug: 'what-is-a-parsec', title: 'What is a parsec?' },
	{ slug: 'what-gaia-measures', title: 'What Gaia measures' }
];
---

<Layout title={`${title} | Learn | Found in Space`}>
	<SiteHeader section="Learn" />

	<main class="page">
		<article class="topic-content">
			<p class="eyebrow">Topic 02</p>
			<h1>{title}</h1>
			<p class="lede">{summary}</p>

			<section class="body">
				<p>
					In the context of a galaxy 100,000 light-years across, our Sun's neighbourhood is an
					extremely small volume. But even "nearby" in space is huge in human terms.
				</p>
				<p>
					The closest star system to our Sun is Alpha Centauri, about 4.37 light-years away.
					The nearest single star, Proxima Centauri, is slightly closer (4.24 light-years).
					If you could travel at the speed of a modern spacecraft (like Voyager 1), it would still
					take about 70,000 years to reach those closest neighbours.
				</p>
				<p>
					When we talk about the "solar neighbourhood," we usually mean the stars within 100
					to 200 light-years. This area—our "local bubble"—is what the Gaia mission is currently
					mapping with incredible detail.
				</p>

				<div class="callout panel">
					<p class="panel__eyebrow">Scale Check</p>
					<h3>A tiny corner of a huge galaxy</h3>
					<p>
						There are hundreds of billions of stars in the Milky Way. We can only really
						"see" and map the local stars with high accuracy. This local region is our small,
						well-measured home in a vast dynamical system.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<TopicSkykitViewer variant="neighbourhood" topic="what-is-nearby-in-space" />

			<TopicNext topics={nextTopics} />
		</article>

		<MadeByKaj />
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.page {
		max-width: 48rem;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 3.2rem 1.5rem 5rem;
	}

	.topic-content {
		padding: 2rem 0;
	}

	.eyebrow {
		margin: 0 0 0.8rem;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.16em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--fis-gold);
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 3.8rem);
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin: 0;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
	}

	.lede {
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: var(--fis-text-soft);
	}

	.body {
		margin-top: 3rem;
	}

	.body p {
		font-size: 1.12rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: var(--fis-text-soft);
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.callout {
		margin: 3rem 0;
		padding: 2rem;
		background: var(--fis-panel);
		border: 1px solid var(--fis-line);
		border-radius: var(--fis-radius);
		backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
	}

	.callout h3 {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		font-size: 1.4rem;
		color: var(--fis-text);
	}

	.panel__eyebrow {
		margin: 0 0 0.8rem;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.16em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--fis-gold);
	}
</style>
